Package space.sunqian.common.third.protobuf

Class ProtobufSchemaHandler

java.lang.Object
space.sunqian.common.third.protobuf.ProtobufSchemaHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
ObjectSchemaParser.Handler
public class ProtobufSchemaHandler extends Object implements ObjectSchemaParser.Handler
ObjectSchemaParser.Handler implementation for Protocol Buffers, can be quickly used through similar codes: 

 ObjectSchemaParser parser = ObjectSchemaParser
     .defaultParser()
     .withFirstHandler(new ProtobufSchemaHandler());
To use this class, the protobuf package com.google.protobuf must in the runtime environment.

Note:

  • When ProtocolStringList is used as a property type, it will be mapped to List<String>, but the type of the instance returned by ObjectProperty.getValue(Object) is still ProtocolStringList;
  • For a Builder, the properties of repeated and map types do not have setter methods, but the setter (which is am Invocable) is not null.

      public boolean parse(@Nonnull ObjectSchemaParser.Context context) throws Exception
      Description copied from interface: ObjectSchemaParser.Handler
      Parses Type to ObjectSchema with its owner parsing logic. The Type is specified by ObjectSchemaParser.Context.dataType() of the given context, and the parsed properties should be stored in ObjectSchemaParser.Context.propertyBaseMap(). Returns false to prevent subsequent handlers to continue to parse, otherwise returns true.
